We will first need to align our assembled genome to a reference genome ( here: channel catfish).

### Alignment using LAST


##first create index of I. Punctatus
~/last-1133/src/lastdb -P4 -uNEAR -R01 Ch.catfish-NEAR Assembly.fasta                      


##Create matrice for substitution and gap frequencies between species
~/last-1133/scriptslast-train -P4 --revsym --matsym --gapsym -E0.05 -C2 Ch.catfish-NEAR Assembly.Ancistrus.fasta > Ict-Anc.mat

##alignment with minimum 1MB length (-l 1000)
~/last-1133/src/lastal -m50 -E0.05 -C2 -l 1000 Ict-Anc.mat Ch.catfish-NEAR Assembly.Ancistrus.fa | last-split -m1 > ict-Anc.maf



##testing
~/last-1133/scripts/last-train -P4 --revsym --matsym --gapsym -E0.05 -C2 Ch.catfish-NEAR ~/wengan/Abc:WenganD,2,SPolished.asm.wengan.fasta> Ict-Anc.test.mat
